- Today’s prices (reference mid-morning):

- Notable market context from news:

  - Nvidia: Longer-term strength in 2025 with potential demand normalization beyond; ongoing strong advanced packaging demand (Digitimes CoWoS tags through Oct).
  - Microsoft: July Q4 FY25 results showed broad Cloud & AI strength; Azure revenue up strongly.
  - Alphabet: DOJ case led to remedies rather than breakup; removes a severe tail-risk; neutral-to-modestly positive.
- Attempted X and Reddit sentiment checks:
  - The X API for historical time windows returned invalid time-range errors for Oct 2–3, 2025, in this environment. Reddit searches also returned no results due to API/availability limitations. I proceeded using corroborated news sources as above.

Step 2 — Portfolio valuation update (post any action below)

Step 3 — Current weights after adjustment

Rationale for the small trim and no further changes today
- Macro/sector: Rotation under way intraday with Nasdaq softness despite broader indices at highs. This argues for slightly reducing outsized exposure to the most cyclical/valuation-sensitive name short term (NVDA), without abandoning the long-term thesis.
- NVDA: Secular demand remains strong through 2025, but near-term multiple sensitivity is elevated amid “AI euphoria” debate and tech-led pullbacks on days like today. A 1-share trim is a risk control move; we keep a large core position (13 shares).
- MSFT: Durable AI + Cloud momentum; antitrust overhang low; fundamentals look steady. Keeping full 4 shares.
- GOOGL: Remedies over breakup in the DOJ case reduces worst-case tail risk. Keeping 1 share.
- Cash raised to ~5.5% increases flexibility to buy on further dips into earnings season if opportunities arise.

Near-term plan and catalysts to watch

- Any NVDA product cadence/Blackwell shipment updates and AI infrastructure demand signals.
- MSFT commentary on Copilot attach and Azure AI consumption.
- Alphabet Q&A on DOJ remedy implementation and ad/search spending trends.
- I will reattempt X and Reddit sentiment queries when the API window allows and adjust if fresh, market-moving signals emerge.
